(4924, 214, 'rows_0_col1', '<h1 class=\"h2\"><span style=\"color: #ff8700;\">Activities</span></h1>\r\nLorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit. Maecenas vehicula nulla sed pellentesque semper. Sed pellentesque massa vel neque tincidunt, eu ultrices augue bibendum. Aliquam ac congue elit. Pellentesque quam arcu, commodo sit amet euismod nec, condimentum at augue. Nulla.\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h2>Winter activities</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-148\" src=\"http://chaletcimbria.honeydigital.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/winter-activities-01.jpg\" alt=\"winter-activities-01\" width=\"1280\" height=\"800\" />\r\nFor those interested in a Winter vacation we are located less than a 10minute walk to the Gondola at Morillon, providing you access to 265sq miles and over 150 runs of skiing. The Grand Massif includes tree lined resorts of Morillon, Samoens, Sixt and Les Carroz as well as easy access to Flaine with high altitude early and late skiing. Ski buses are close by enabling you alternative access to other gondolas in Samoens and Vercland as well as car free freedom to tour around the area. If you want to stay for longer than a couple of weeks within a short drive you have access to the Portes du Soleil via Les Gets, Morzine and Avoriaz. If skiing is not your activity there are plenty of snowshoe walking routes in the area, ice skating in Samoens and dog sledding at Les Carroz. We have teamed up with local company that will bring your preordered skis, boots and helmets to the Chalet at your agreed time and then collect them when you are finished. Say goodbye to long queues for Skis and focus on your holiday.\r\n\r\n<a class=\"primary-link\" href=\"#\">Book your ski/board hire (free delivery to your door)</a>\r\n\r\n<a class=\"primary-link\" href=\"#\">Book ski lessons</a>\r\n\r\n<a class=\"primary-link\" href=\"#\">Ski area and maps</a>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h2>Summer activities</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-151\" src=\"http://chaletcimbria.honeydigital.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/summer-activities-01.jpg\" alt=\"summer-activities\" width=\"1280\" height=\"800\" />\r\nThe Summer months offer even greater possibilities with activities including; Walking and Hiking with, short and easy walks to more challenging day hikes within the Giffre Valley or access to some of the great longer distance paths including those towards Chamonix and Mont Blanc. The immediate area has some great road cycling and MTB routes for all levels and local hire shops enable you to hire the latest MTB bikes suitable for all ages and capabilities. Walking and cycle routes can be accessed directly from the property, with a short drive providing access to unlimited possibilities. White Water rafting, kayaking and paragliding can all be booked via local companies and offer a great personalised service. Within a 10minute walk across local footpaths you have access to a freshwater swimming lake with local beach and diving platforms and high ropes for both children and adults. The lake offers the ultimate end of day place to relax after a hard days walking, soaking up the last of the afternoon sun and access to a restaurant cafe serving ice cold beers and wine for adults and soft drinks and ices for kids.\r\n\r\nThe pretty town of Samoens can be reached by walking (30mins) or cycling (10mins) along the Giffre River or an easy 5min drive. During the Winter season the town has regular events and activities on as well as family friendly Apres Ski theme. In the summer you have access to a fishing lake, large park with football and tennis courts as well as outside swimming pools.\r\n\r\nThe beautiful town of Sixt-Fer-à-Cheval nestles at the end of the Giffre Valley. A member of the most beautiful villages in France within a designated area of outstanding natural beauty Sixt offers a great day out. Including gentle strolls along the valley floor beside glacial blue rivers, hikes to peaceful mountain restaurants serving simple and mouth-watering food or admiring the abundance of waterfalls including the mighty Cascade du Rouget. In the summer, you can take an easy end of day road ride to the village, along a steady low incline road and free wheel the way home.\r\n\r\n<a class=\"primary-link\" href=\"#\">White water rafting</a>\r\n\r\n<a class=\"primary-link\" href=\"#\">Book lessons</a>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h2>Days Out</h2>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-104 size-full\" src=\"http://chaletcimbria.honeydigital.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/Alpage-de-la-Vieille-Laurent-Ferrari-3.jpg\" alt=\"Alpage-de-la-Vieille-Laurent-Ferrari-3\" width=\"1920\" height=\"1280\" />\r\nChamonix - Home to Mont Blanc and the UTMB, amazing old valley town with great walking &amp; climbing shops and opportunities to see and up close a number of mighty glaciers or experience an old-fashioned rail journey up the mountain.\r\n\r\nAnnecy - A glorious historic lakeside city adjacent to one of the largest freshwater lakes in Europe. You can spend a day either shopping in chic and trendy shops, sampling the abundance of restaurants and glace shops or just taking a leisurely cruise on one of the many boats (Think Bond ……) For those wanting something with more action there are local beaches, pedaloes, and even open water swimming routes.\r\n\r\nSixt-Fer-à-Cheval - The beautiful town nestles at the end of the Giffre Valley. A member of the most beautiful villages in France within a designated area of outstanding natural beauty Sixt offers a great day out. Including gentle strolls along the valley floor beside glacial blue rivers, hikes to peaceful mountain restaurants serving simple and mouth-watering food or admiring the abundance of waterfalls including the mighty Cascade du Rouget.\r\n\r\nGeneva – Adjacent to the largest freshwater lake in Europe and surrounded by cultural places to visit you can spend many days in Geneva. For the day you can visit the old town, take a tour of St Pierre Cathedral, jump on a cruise on the lake or go and vist CERN the headquarters for the European Organization for Nuclear Research. Its many parks and open spaces provide a great location for picnic lunches or just sample a rich mix of restaurants.'),
