(5372, 225, 'rows_0_col1', '<h1 class=\"h2\"><span style=\"color: #ff8700;\">Holidays &amp; Short Breaks</span></h1>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-169\" src=\"http://chaletcimbria.honeydigital.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/local-information-01.jpg\" alt=\"local-information-01\" width=\"1280\" height=\"800\" />\r\n<h3>Family Holidays</h3>\r\nMorillon is an amazing family resort, with access to guaranteed snow in the winter for all levels and a good blend of French (link to ESF) and English (link to ZigZag) speaking schools.\r\n\r\nFor those less inclined to ski/board there is snowshoe walking, dog sledges, ice skating, indoor bowling and all day Spa’s. In the summer you are on the doorstep to some of the best walking and biking routes in France and the family resort theme extends to the local fresh water swimming lake that can be reached by you and the children across footpaths in under 10minutes; a great way to chill or cool off after a full on day in the valley. Only 1 hr from Geneva and easy access within an hour to great places including Geneva, Chamonix, Courmayeur and Annecy.\r\n\r\n<a class=\"primary-link\" href=\"http://www.ot-morillon.fr/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">For more on Morillon: www.morillon.fr</a>\r\n\r\nOur Chalet is owned by an outdoor loving family and is setup to provide a comfortable and relaxed stay for families both small and large. A great location for some fun in the mountains for families that want to provide an amazing experience for themselves and their children.\r\n\r\n[gallery link=\"none\" columns=\"2\" size=\"large\" ids=\"171,172\"]\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h3>Short Breaks</h3>\r\nFor those wanting a short break Morillon and the Grand Massiff has everything you need and all on your door step. Only 1 hour away from Geneva airport you can be assured to maximise your time off doing what you want rather than travelling.\r\n\r\nDuring the winter groups can experience skiing for all abilities, outside of school holidays the Grand Massiff remains the hidden gem within France. With quite slopes and restaurants you can make the most of easy cruise blues or more extreme reds and blacks and some extensive off piste. For those not wanting skiing / boarding there are snowshoe walks, dog sledging, horse riding and fat biking as well as local all day spas for those wanting a pamper.\r\n\r\nIn the summer you can make the most of great days out on the mix of MTB trails or road cycling, either thru the valley or follow the route of the legendary Tour de France, leading through Morillon and Samoens and up the Col Ju Plane towards Les Gets. Morillon is ideal for walking with access to walking routes linking mountain lodges and restaurants for longer all day walks or just grab your pack for some exhilarating views across to Mt Blanc, surrounding valleys and Sixt-Fer-à-Cheval where the River Giffre starts its life, fed by the snow and local Glaciers. To complete your short break make the most of the White Water rafting via local teams in Morillon or Paragliding from the top of Samoens.\r\n\r\nOur Chalet is owned by an outdoor loving family and is setup to provide a comfortable and relaxed stay for all groups both small and large. A great location for adult groups looking for some fun in the mountains and wanting to get away and experience the real mountains.\r\n\r\n[gallery link=\"none\" columns=\"2\" size=\"large\" ids=\"171,172\"]'),
